              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "4-BE-10",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.05
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A BeO target, 75+-8 microg/cm2",
                "thick (1.36+- 0.35 microg/cm2 of 10Be), on a 5.7+-",
                "0.4-mg/cm2 Pt foil, was mounted on a stainless-steel",
                "holder and placed in a small chamber with the BeO",
                "upstream on the foil. Beryllium enriched to 5% in",
                "10Be has been extracted from neutron-irradiated",
                "carbon, and has been used for targets in nuclear",
                "spectroscopy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
